  "doc_id": "40577",
  "text": "To recognize motion is a relatively simple task and for many diagnostic applications a simple \"burglar alarm\" type of application may be sufficient. A number of smartphone apps may be useful e.g., for recognition of Strongyloides worms in stools. Numerous tracking algorithms have been published [CITATION_1] and new ones like LOCOMOTIS [CITATION_2] allow for inexpensive tracking analysis. More advanced signal processing was achieved through the approach of Kaakinen et al. [CITATION_3] . The degree of sophistication required obviously depends on what type of information is required. The image analysis process we used aimed at highly specific target identification based on motility time and frequency signal processing. Observed motility patterns might then serve as \"diagnostic fingerprints.\" Our results suggest that this is achievable.",
